# 🛒 Kroger API Usage Guide

This guide provides step-by-step instructions on how to:
- 🔑 Obtain an **OAuth2 Access Token** from Kroger's API
- 🏬 Retrieve **store locations**
- 🛍 Fetch **product details** (requires explicit scope)

📌 **Official Kroger API Documentation:**  
[Product API Documentation](https://developer.kroger.com/api-products/api/product-api-public#tag/Products/operation/productGet)

---

## **Get an OAuth2 Access Token**
To interact with Kroger’s API, you need to obtain a **valid access token**.
Ask merel@loopdash.com for client_id and client_secret

### 🔹 **Basic Token Request**
Use this command to request an access token **without additional scopes**:

```sh
curl -X POST \
  'https://api.kroger.com/v1/connect/oauth2/token' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded' \
  -H 'Authorization: Basic <YOUR_BASE64_ENCODED_CLIENT_ID:CLIENT_SECRET>' \
  -d 'grant_type=client_credentials'
```
Sometimes, you have to specify product scope in the oauth call above

```sh
curl -X POST \
  'https://api.kroger.com/v1/connect/oauth2/token' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded' \
  -H 'Authorization: Basic <YOUR_BASE64_ENCODED_CLIENT_ID:CLIENT_SECRET>' \
  -d 'grant_type=client_credentials&scope=product.compact'
```
## **Get Product Data**
 
Example, use Kroger Milk at locationId 01400943
```sh
curl -X GET \
  'https://api.kroger.com/v1/products?filter.term=milk&filter.brand=Kroger&filter.locationId=01400943&filter.limit=10' \                
  -H 'Accept: application/json' \
  -H 'Authorization: Bearer <YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN>' \
  --output response-unrig-kroger-milk-location01400943.json
```